1.  GRANT OF LICENSE

a. The GigE-V Framework for Linux (the "Licensed Software") is an SDK intended 
   for developing imaging applications using TELEDYNE DALSA image acquisition 
   and processing hardware. The Licensed Software consists of a series of 
   open source libraries that links to a static binary library containing 
   functions providing the basic communciation protocols of the GigE Vision
   standard.


b. The Licensed Software is not designed for use in on-line control equipment
   in hazardous environments such as operation of nuclear facilities, 
   aircraft navigation or control, or direct life support machines.

c. You have a right to reproduce, and distribute, in object code form and 
   solely as part of your installation system, any installation executable 
   files and object libraries included with the Licensed Software, provided 
   you 
